SBM takes 75 per cent of Chase deposits, liabilities The Central Bank of Kenya (CBK) on Tuesday unveiled a tax-free, 15-year infrastructure bond that will be listed at the Nairobi Securities Exchange (NSE). “The Central Bank of Kenya, acting in its capacity as fiscal agent for the Republic of Kenya, invites bids for the above bond,” said CBK of the bond that would be sold between January 22 and January 23, this year.